h3. Summary

The display of time zones in Team Calendars is inconsistent with [ISO 8601 standards|http://www.iso.org/iso/home/standards/iso8601.htm]. 

h3. Environment
* Team Calendars 5.3.10

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to Calendars and click Add Calendar
# Time zone is displayed in alphabetical order
{panel}
|Time zone|Australia/Sydney (+1100)|
{panel}
# Click the ellipsis menu on a calendar
# Select Edit
# Time zone is displayed in alphabetical order
{panel}
|Time zone|Australia/Sydney (+1100)|
{panel}

h3. Expected Results
* Time zone should display in time zone order and with correct formatting
{panel}
|Time zone|AEDT Australian Eastern Daylight Time (UTC+11)|
{panel}

h3. Actual Results
* Time zone is displayed in alphabetical order
{panel}
|Time zone|Australia/Sydney (+1100)|
{panel}

h3. Notes
Confluence also has issues with the display of time zones.

h3.Workaround
No workaround.

